description: For sale: $345,000. Lake Vermilion all-season CABIN with a fantastic water view of Pike Bay!!!! This charming cabin has been cared for by one family over the years, offering a cozy  feeling with the openness provided by abundant windows. The cabin has had many updates including insulated metal roof, a deep well, an enlarged septic, new thermopane windows throughout, furnace, central heating, a large walk-out bedroom on the lower level, a 2 stall garage. Recent additions are stainless steel appliances, and newly painted exterior and decks. This year-round cabin accommodates both summer and winter retreats. There is a bunkhouse for additional guests or for solitary getaways. The cabin is surrounded by a healthy forest with 2.5 acres of mature white & red pine, birch and maple. For swimming, fishing or boating, there is a 45 ' L-shaped cedar dock with a bench, a flagpole and a boat lift. An open deck system accents the front of the cabin and is the perfect place to enjoy the preserved natural shoreline.

description: For sale: $575,900. LAKE VERMILION Exceptional year around home on Birch Point, one of Lake Vermilion's most distinguished and desirable locations. description: Recently sold: $141,900. Tucked under an impressive stand of old growth white pines is this move-in ready home on the edge of town. This main floor living home has three bedrooms and an open floor plan.  All the updates are done, including new appliances in the kitchen, utility sink, extra pantry, garage shelving, and patio with a hot tub.  The house is energy efficient utilizing in-floor heat in both the house and the garage; and a wood stove in the living room keeps the house cozy warm during the shoulder seasons.  Two window air conditioners keep you cool in the summer!  You can move in and start enjoying the "Up North".  An easy to maintain, spacious yard with wild raspberries and strawberries, vegetable, morel mushroom and native flower gardens and bonfire area will be enjoyed by the whole family.  The hot tub on the back patio is a perfect place to view the stars and relax after a day of playing outside. There is plenty of space in the heated two-car garage, large shed and extensive driveway to stow or park your toys, snowmobiles, campers, bikes, boats and 4-wheelers!  The garage has been updated with 220 volt/50 amp and would be perfect for a shop.
